y representative, he will usually\ntry to persuade you that hit company\u2014and only his\ncompany\u2014is best for you.\nThat in fact is a good reason for buying insurance only\nthrough an independent insurance agent or broker\nV Became he represent* noi one hut several insurance cam\npanic* he can be impartial in picking the be*t company\nfor your individual need*.\nV Because ha't a proleuional insurance man, not just a sales*\nman. he keeps up with new types of insurance coverage\nand makes certain your insurance is up to date.\nV Because ha is independent you can count on him to assist\nyou with your claim when you suffer a lots and to repre\ntent your interests to the fullest at all limes.\nOur advice: To he certain about your insurance\nprotection and service, see us who are independent\nbrokers.\nBusiness Established 1926\nJ. Blais# do Sibour I Go.\ne e\nInsurance Broken\n1700 Eye St. N.W. ME. 1-3996\nI *\u00abn**. tire. lelant rr\u00ab*innrt\u00abfin\u00bb verei, Pretoria, floaters, AuMmrtiiir\nas* Ctnrallr /stvrasrt\nMore Gains\nAnticipated\nFor Housing\nHEW YORK. J*n. 4\nHousing today Is s bright spot\n|in s cloudy\u2014but not necessarily\ndark\u2014economic picture.\nAt the moment non-farm\nresidential building Is recover\ning from a mild two-year de\ncline and most economists be\nlieve the recovery will continue\nThey base this forecast on:\nPint, there ought to be more\nmoney around this year for the\nbuilding and buying of homee.\nSecond, the demand for funds\nfrom sources other than hous\ning Is likely to decline. The\ntremendous expansion program\nof large corporations In the\npast few yean drained money\naway from housing and helped\nj force up Interest rates.\nExgawden Flans Dreg\nNow. according to forecasta,\ncorporations do not plan aa\nheavy capital expenditures In'\n195* as In 1957. They\u2019ll need\nto borrow less iponey.\nThird, there are such factors\nas continuing population\ngrowth (about three million\npersons s year), relatively high\nhousehold formations '850.000\na year), low housing vacancies\nand potential demand from\nhome owners displaced by the\ngigantic national highway pro\ngram.\nFinally, the Housing Act of\n195? lowered minimum down\npayment requirements on FHA\ninsured loans on s house with\nan FHA valuation of 130.000.\nthe new minimum down pay\nment Is $3,400 compared with\n13,200 under the previous law.\nInterest rates were Increased\nfrom 5 to 8V\u00ab per cent.\nBuilding Picked Up\nIn 1957 building of new\nhomes got off to a compara\ntively poor start and there was\nmuch sound and fury from the\nbuilding trade associations.\nBut. starting in May. the trend\nstarted to pick up.\nIn the third quarter housing\nstarts averaged more tnan\n990.000 units a year. While\nthe number of starts In the\nfirst nine months of 1957 was\nthe lowest since 1949. decline*\nfrom the year-earlier rate nar\nrowed steadily from 18 per cent\nearly in 1957 to 10 per cent at\nthe end of the third quarter\n_\nMachine Tool\nLag Mounts\nCLEVELAND. Jan. 4\nThe machine tool industry, one\nof the important barometers of\nbusiness activity, saw a sharp\ndecline In new business In 1957\nNo pickup is expected in the\nfirst quarter of 1958. Alter that,\nthe picture depends largely on\nthe prospect of orders from the\nauto industry and the Defense\nDepartment.\nThere has been a steady drop\nIn new orders. A year ago the\nsix-day week was common In\nthe Industry. Now most em\nployes are on s five or four\nday week.\nThe National Machine Tool\nBuilders\u2019 Association said the\nnew order figure for October\nwas only 837.850.000 compared\nwith 863.2 million last January\nThe association estimated\nnew orders of tools for 1957\namounted to 8525 million com\npared with $924 million In 1956\nThe 1955 total was 892? 1 mil\nlion: the 1954 total was $514,-\n450.000\nAluminum Sales Rise\nNEW YORK. Jan. 4 (Ah\u2014\nSales of aluminum building\nmaterials have been rising and\nthe prospect is that 1958 will\nbe one of the best 